tr: having the sticky properties of an adhesive

example: awkward (or embarrassing or difficult) moments in the discussion
an awkward pause followed his remark
in the unenviable position of resorting to an act he had planned to save for the climax of the campaign

tr: moist as with undried perspiration and with clothing sticking to the body
example: felt sticky and chilly at the same time

value.def: A sticky substance is soft, or thick and liquid, and can stick to other things. Sticky things are covered with a sticky substance.

example.ex: If the dough is sticky, add more flour...
example.tran: 如果面团太黏，就再加点面粉。

value.tran: 黏性的;涂有黏性物质的

value.def: A sticky situation involves problems or is embarrassing.

example.ex: Inevitably the transition will yield some sticky moments...
example.tran: 过渡时期难免会出现一些困难的时候。

example.ex: Her research was going through a sticky patch.
example.tran: 她的研究工作正处于一个艰难的阶段。

value.def: Sticky weather is unpleasantly hot and damp.

example.ex: ...four desperately hot, sticky days in the middle of August.
example.tran: 8 月中旬极其闷热的 4 天

value.def: If someone comes to a sticky end or meets a sticky end, they suffer very badly or die in an unpleasant way.

example.ex: Arminius also came to a sticky end, murdered by his own troops.
example.tran: 阿米尼乌斯也死得很惨，被自己的部下害死了。
